reviewText: The sound quality is just awful, and Chet isn't playing very well. Chet is sitting on a couch and playing into a cheap mic. The Tokyo concert with Harold Danko and Jon Engels, identified as 1987, is a LOT nicer (although the picture quality isn't very good). The Jazz Icons DVD is also a winner.
Rare DVD of one of the jazz greats, trumpet & singing, I had not known existed. Good price and fast service.
